<L>__{exterior hotel forecourt. day}
<A>__{paul waits, then a car pulls up, an indian businessman, mr. garindi, gets out, shakes hands, he's shaken.}
<C>__{mr. garindi}
<D>__{terrible times, paul. there are bodies everywhere. i cannot stay here.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{i need a great favor.}
<A>__{he hands mr. garindi an address.}
<C>__{paul }
<D>__{i need you to go to this address and bring my brother in law and his family.}
<C>__{mr. garindi}
<D>__{no, no. this is a very dangerous part of town. i cannot do this.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{this would be an enormous favor to me. i am a man of means, mr. garandi. when this nonsense is over i will be most grateful.}
